<br>
There will be vendors and shops there selling or rep'ing their equipment. A friend of mine bought a new name brand rod for 1/2 its standard list price. One of the advantages to a show of this sort is being able to see what is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>available</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. Most of the factory reps will have the newest and greatest thing in their various lines at the conclave. You can get advise and information that you can't get anywhere else.<br>
<br>
Information and education are the real commodities at a conclave. You have the opportunity to network with fly fishers that may have either more or different experiences from your own. There are tons of classes available on everything from fly tying, casting, to rod building, and actual fishing technique. Personally, I'll be taking a casting clinic with Bill Gammel. I'll also be giving free casting lessons along with about 10 other instructors. There will be several dozen fly tyers available. I like to see what people are tying and pick up any new techniques I can.<br>
<br>
Fly fishers are a different breed in the first place. We have a degree of difficulty in learning from someone else but would rather learn on our own. Guys with considerable experience often get into a mode where they really don't want to ask questions like it might call into question their abilities. These conclaves are a great place to have a non-threatening learning environment. For anyone who has never been to one you'll find yourself better from the experience.<br>
<br>
John <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=randy@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>randy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#000000>(9/23/03 8:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=128.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> sff conclave</span><hr size=1> I'll have a merchandise from The Woodsman in Fort Smith at the Conclave....New rods and reels...waders, etc.  2003 stuff but it's new just stuff I need to get rid of for the new season coming up....stop by and give me a holla...I doubt i'll get to fish that weekend because I'll be working.  But I'll be on the Norfork Oct 31, Nov1, and Nov 2nd.  I can't wait <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=flysoup>flysoup</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#000000>(9/23/03 9:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=128.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sff conclave</span><hr size=1> Howdy Glowworm,<br>
